  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective of the study is to establish the prevalence of lower extremity
      peripheral arterial disease (PAD), defined as an ankle-brachial index of less than or equal
      to 0.9, in subjects with at least two of the specified cardiovascular disease (CVD) risk
      factors, with no overt cardiovascular disease.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
